flowRoot.flowPara: The primary role of the HIG is to enable people to design high-quality, integrated and consistent applications for the GNOME platform. It also serves a secondary role in helping new GNOME contributors to learn the project's design goals and approaches.

These Human Interface Guidelines (HIG) will help you to create application designs for GNOME 3. They provide assistance in ensuring that your application is properly integrated with GNOME 3, is consistent with other GNOME 3 applications, and delivers great user experiences.
a small set of pages containing essential design advice and rules.
A larger collection of building blocks that you can use to design your application.

The design patterns include a variety of different design elements that you can utilise. Some patterns describe individual user interface components, such as check boxes or lists. Others describe more complex arrangements of components.
